# rethunk-git MCP (this workspace)

This project registers **rethunk-git** via [`.cursor/mcp.json`](.cursor/mcp.json) (local `bun src/server.ts`). Cursor supplies workspace roots at MCP initialize; do not rely on a fixed `cwd` in config.

## When to use it

- Before describing repo or multi-root git state, or when batching commits across paths, call **MCP tools** instead of shell `git status`, `git log`, or ad-hoc loops:
  - **`rethunk-git_git_status`** — root + submodule-style sweep (`allWorkspaceRoots`, `rootIndex`, optional `format: "json"`)
  - **`rethunk-git_git_inventory`** — status and ahead/behind per root (default upstream `@{u}`; pass `remote`+`branch` together for fixed tracking; `nestedRoots`, `preset`, `presetMerge`, `maxRoots`, `format`)
  - **`rethunk-git_git_parity`** — compare `HEAD` across path pairs (`pairs`, `preset`, `presetMerge`, `format`)
  - **`rethunk-git_list_presets`** — discover `.rethunk/git-mcp-presets.json` entries and validation errors
- Resource **`rethunk-git://presets`** — JSON view of presets at the resolved git toplevel when clients support MCP resources

## When shell git is still fine

- One-off commands the tools do not cover (e.g. `git diff`, `git cherry-pick`), or when the MCP server is unavailable after a failed reload.

If MCP tools are missing from the session, remind the user to **reload MCP** or run **`bun install`** so `bun` resolves.
